<CSSMargin-top>
<summary>
The <strong><c>margin-top</c></strong> <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS">CSS</see> property sets the <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/CSS_box_model/Introduction_to_the_CSS_box_model#margin_area">margin area</see> on the top of an element. A positive value places it farther from its neighbors, while a negative value places it closer.
</summary>
<remarks>
<para>EmbedInteractiveExample("pages/css/margin-top.html")</para><para>This property has no effect on <strong>non-</strong><strong><see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/Replaced_element">replaced</see></strong> inline elements, such as <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/span">span</see> or <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/code">code</see>.</para>
<para>-<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/margin-right">margin-right</see>, <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/margin-bottom">margin-bottom</see>, and <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/margin-left">margin-left</see> and the <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/margin">margin</see> shorthand<br/>-The mapped logical properties: <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/margin-block-start">margin-block-start</see>, <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/margin-block-end">margin-block-end</see>, <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/margin-inline-start">margin-inline-start</see>, and <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/margin-inline-end">margin-inline-end</see> and the shorthands <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/margin-block">margin-block</see> and <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/margin-inline">margin-inline</see><br/></para>
<para><seealso href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/margin-top"> <em>See also on MDN</em> </seealso></para>
</remarks>
</CSSMargin-top>
